<item>
            <title>[LUDOC-474] Add content regarding modifying a non-default quota to the default quota.</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LUDOC-474</link>
                <project id="10070" key="LUDOC">Lustre Documentation</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Lustre documentation (section 25.4.1) provides examples of how to set quotas for users, groups, &amp;amp; projects without needing to explicitly set quotas on each entity.&#160; Great feature, btw!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That section also demonstrates how to disable the default user/group/project quotas.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Given that a u/g/p could have a non-default quota, could we add an example of how to revert a non-default u/g/p quota to the default u/g/p quota?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The following seem to set specific user/group/project quotas to use the default quota limits:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ol&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lfs setquota -d -u user1 /scratch&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lfs setquota -d -g group1 /scratch&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;lfs setquota -d -p project1 /scratch&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ol&gt;


&lt;p&gt;That ability is identified in the lfs setquota usage, and also in the lfs-setquota man page, but thinking it might be helpful to have an example of the -d option somewhere in/around section 25.4.1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
